\subsection{11.11.1 What is form-FORCED}

\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{The functional form $G = c^3\ell_P^2/\hbar$.} Newton's gravitational constant as a relationship among substrate constants.
\item \textbf{The functional form $a_0 = c\,H_0/(2\pi)$.} MOND transition acceleration with the $2\pi$ as dipole azimuthal period.
\item \textbf{The geometric-mean form of ECR.} $a = \sqrt{a_N\,a_0}$ in the deep-MOND regime as substrate's multiplicative-participation rule.
\item \textbf{The slope-4 form of Tully–Fisher.} $v^4 = G\,M\,a_0$ from T19+T20+ECR with orbital balance.
\item \textbf{Flat rotation curves.} Corollary of T21.
\item \textbf{The asymptotic constraints on the modified Poisson equation interpolation function.} $\mu \to 1$ at high acceleration (Newton recovered); $\mu \to x$ at low acceleration (ECR recovered).
