Each is a bounded structural extension of Chapter 7's QC architectural content. None requires new substrate primitives.

\subsection{15.9.6 Three O items from Arc BH}

Three O items carry forward from Arc BH:

\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{O1: superradiance amplitude derivation.} Structurally compatible with BH-6's substrate-level reading; full amplitude derivation requires extending BH-6 + Arc SG.
\item \textbf{O2: closed-form $\log g$.} Part of the closed-form-substrate-constants program (Section 15.9.2).
\item \textbf{O3: full Kerr interior audit.} BH-3 establishes saturated-zone interior structure for Schwarzschild-class BHs; rotating-BH interior architecture (ergosphere, Cauchy horizons, frame-dragging at saturation) requires extension.
