\subsection{15.9.7 Arc COSMO — speculative-not-refuted}

\textbf{Arc COSMO} is the cosmic-expansion / $H_0$-from-substrate program. The structural target: derive cosmic expansion at substrate level, including possible substrate-level Friedmann-class equations, $H_0$ derivation, expansion-history dynamics, $\Lambda$ value, Hubble tension.

The content:
\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{Substrate-level cosmic-horizon dynamics.} Currently the cosmic horizon enters T20 (Chapter 11) as a substrate input characterizing distance $R_H = c/H_0$; Arc COSMO would derive the cosmic-horizon dynamics from substrate primitives.
\item \textbf{$H_0$ from substrate.} Currently the Hubble rate is a substrate input; Arc COSMO would derive $H_0$ from substrate constants.
\item \textbf{Hubble tension.} The 67-versus-73 km/s/Mpc empirical disagreement may have a substrate-level structural origin reachable from the framework's primitives.
\end{itemize}

Arc COSMO is \textbf{speculative-not-refuted}. The framework treats it as a long-horizon target; current substrate-level scope does not yet include the substrate-level cosmological-scale dynamics required to address it. Possible scope: 15–25 memos if pursued.

\subsection{15.9.8 GR-4A — Einstein-equation emergence (speculative-not-refuted)}

\textbf{GR-4A} is the program's name for the question of whether full Einstein-equation emergence is reachable from substrate primitives. The framework's curvature-emergence content (Chapter 12, Arc ED-10) closes at acoustic-metric scalar-tensor level; the acoustic metric is kinematic, not the dynamical metric of Einstein's theory. GR-4A asks whether the kinematic content can be promoted to genuine dynamical metric content.

The status:
\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{Speculative-not-refuted.} Promotion to full GR requires either a new substrate primitive or a derivation strategy not yet identified.
\item \textbf{If forced}, the framework becomes a gravity theory at field-equation level.
\item \textbf{If refuted}, the kinematic ceiling is permanent; the framework remains at Arc ED-10's acoustic-metric scalar-tensor level for relativistic-gravity content.
\end{itemize}

The Arc ED-10 closure (Chapter 12) sharpens GR-4A's structural obstruction at the acoustic-metric kinematic-versus-dynamical level; future GR-4A work targets converting the kinematic content into genuine dynamical content.

