\item \textbf{ED-I-23 (Josephson Junctions)} — Multiplicity at engineered low-$\mathcal{M}$ regions. Demonstrates the substrate-level mechanism by which engineered low-multiplicity regions sustain phase-coherent participation across a junction.
\item \textbf{ED-I-29 (Tunneling)} — Sparse-$\sigma$ regions and global rule reconfiguration. Connects the gradient-sparsity invariant $\sigma$ to the substrate-level mechanism of tunneling as a sparse-$\sigma$ rule reconfiguration rather than barrier penetration.
