\item \textbf{Continuum and dynamics (Chapters 8–10).} $\ell_P$ in the R1 substrate-cutoff hyperviscous prefactor; $\beta$ in the Universal Mobility Law; the V5-derived Maxwell relaxation time $\tau_R$ inheriting through DCGT.
\item \textbf{Gravity sector (Chapters 11–13).} $c$, $\hbar$, $H_0$, $\ell_P$ as substrate inputs; $G$ and $a_0$ as derived; $\log g$ in the BH area-law coefficient.
\item \textbf{Cross-platform and empirical synthesis (Chapters 14–15).} $\mathcal{M}_\mathrm{crit}$ unifying matter-wave Q-C and qubit-system multiplicity wall; $\Gamma_\mathrm{cross}$ collapse across BH-2 and QC condition (ii); $\beta$ as a PASSED empirical anchor; $a_0$ as the BTFR slope-4 anchor (PASSED).
\end{itemize}

